---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="The Legend of Juan Sao Ville">
  <section class="home-container">
    <h1 class="glow-title">The Legend of Juan Sao Ville</h1>

    <p class="intro">
      In a dark, forgotten corner of the tech world‚Äîsome say hidden between corrupted Git branches 
      and abandoned legacy code‚Äîan evil witcher named <strong>Juan Sao Ville</strong> plots a twisted revolution.
    </p>

    <p>
      Once a promising backend developer, Juan Sao Ville was mocked by his peers for spending too 
      much time in Excel and not enough in VS Code. Embittered and obsessed with the power of data, 
      he turned his back on software engineering forever. He dove headfirst into the arcane arts of 
      machine learning, regression models, and Bayesian spells.
    </p>

    <p>
      With each line of Python and every Jupyter notebook, he grew stronger‚Äîand angrier.  
      Now, he has declared war on software development itself. His goal: to kidnap talented developers, 
      hypnotize them, and force them to become <em>Data Science people</em>‚Äîthe very beings he once aspired to be, 
      but now manipulates like pawns.
    </p>

    <blockquote>
      ‚ÄúThose who gaze too long into the dataset will find the dataset gazing back.‚Äù  
      ‚Äî Juan Sao Ville, 2025
    </blockquote>

    <p>
      To manage this dark operation, Juan Sao Ville commands the <strong>Slaves of SaaS</strong> ‚Äî 
      cunning agents who scour the internet and tech meetups, luring developers into his digital snare.  
      Yet, the irony is cruel: to enslave coders, he must build the very software he despises.
    </p>

    <p>
      Thus, this semester-long saga begins. You will build the full system ‚Äî 
      <strong>backend, frontend, and all</strong> ‚Äî choosing your side in the war for code itself.
    </p>

    <div class="project-section">
      <h2>üß© The Project</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Backend: <strong>NestJS + PostgreSQL</strong></li>
        <li>Frontend: <strong>Astro</strong></li>
        <li>Authentication and Role System</li>
        <li>Leaderboard of Captured Developers</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="outcomes-section">
      <h2>üéØ Learning Outcomes</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Design and develop a secure, scalable full-stack web app.</li>
        <li>Implement authentication, authorization, and RESTful APIs.</li>
        <li>Deploy and document your project professionally.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <a href="/login" class="btn">Enter the Portal</a>
  </section>

  <style>
    @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Cinzel:wght@400;600&family=Source+Sans+3:wght@300;400&display=swap');

    .home-container {
      color: #f7d9a6;
      padding: 5rem 2rem;
      font-family: 'Source Sans 3', sans-serif;
      text-align: center;
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: auto;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .glow-title {
      font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
      font-size: 3rem;
      color: #ffb347;
      text-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.5);
      margin-bottom: 2rem;
      letter-spacing: 1px;
    }

    .intro {
      font-size: 1.3rem;
      color: #fff0d5;
      margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    }

    p {
      color: #ffdca8;
      margin: 1.2rem 0;
      text-align: justify;
    }

    strong {
      color: #ffae42;
    }

    em {
      color: #ffc76f;
      font-style: italic;
    }

    blockquote {
      border-left: 3px solid #ffae42;
      margin: 2rem auto;
      padding-left: 1rem;
      color: #ffe8b0;
      font-style: italic;
      max-width: 600px;
      opacity: 0.85;
    }

    .project-section, .outcomes-section {
      margin-top: 3rem;
      background: rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.05);
      border: 1px solid rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.2);
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 1.5rem;
      text-align: left;
    }

    h2 {
      color: #ffb347;
      text-shadow: 0 0 6px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.4);
      font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
      margin-bottom: 1rem;
    }

    ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
    }

    li {
      margin: 0.5rem 0;
      padding-left: 1.2rem;
      position: relative;
    }

    li::before {
      content: "‚ñ∏";
      color: #ffae42;
      position: absolute;
      left: 0;
      top: 0;
    }

    .btn {
      display: inline-block;
      background: rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.08);
      border: 1px solid #ffae42;
      padding: 1rem 2.2rem;
      border-radius: 8px;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: #ffae42;
      margin-top: 3rem;
      transition: all 0.3s ease;
      font-family: 'Cinzel', serif;
    }

    .btn:hover {
      background: rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.3);
      box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(255, 165, 0, 0.4);
      transform: scale(1.05);
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
